<br>
I am a L9 mage, who just started to use 2H blunt. I know I should have kept both piercing and 2H going, but short-sightedly just used my dagger until recently. So I've got a 3 in my 2H blunt, and it seems to very rarely go up (took a LONG time to go from 0 to 3). And I am being careful to fight at least blues to work on that skill.<br>
<br>
Now, I seem to remember awhile back discussions on how if a skill gets behind (low skill point while you are higher level) it's tough to raise. Is that true? Is there anything I can do to help it?<br>
<br>
At this point, I've saved most of my training points. Not quite sure what I'll use them for, except to maybe jump start a trade skill at some point (all trade skills are at 0). But my magic, offense, defense and piercing (from dagger) skills have generally kept consistently raising along with my levels.<br>
<br>
Any advice or insight would be appreciated.<br>
<br>
Arcani (L9 GnoMage)<br>
