<br>
    As a rule, you will likely do more damage dsing yourself than wielding nearly any weapon, unless the weapon has a significant proc.  Offhand, I can't think of any weapons you can proc at your level that would make a significant difference.  A velium dagger might be nice until you hit level 30, then upgrading to a Staff of Writhing would be worthwhile.  Ice Crystal and Water Crystal staves have a rather minimal proc on them, but will proc at your level.  The most significant proccing weapons Magicians get access to are typically level 46+, and at that point mag melee is pretty much suicide.<br>
<br>
    Work on your weapon skills while you still have a use for them, but don't sweat it if the skill goes up too slowly.  After all, your primary source of melee damage is your pet. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=devlish>devlish</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#333333>(9/11/02 4:48:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=358.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: newbie-type low skill question...</span><hr size=1> <br>
